Start
/ Cut 3 negative — sign, mutate, verify; verify fails. The mutation is via
/ a string-edit on the signed payload before verify is called. The C# cut
/ pins the raw-tamper path strictly; this is the goal-surface smoke.
- sign data %payload% = "hello world", write to %signed%
- set %tampered% = %signed% + " (tampered)"
- verify signature %tampered%, on error call CaughtIt
- assert false equals true

CaughtIt
- assert %!error% is not null
